    "body": "@noeliaSD see my comment here https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/11147#issuecomment-1601720373\r\n\r\nMy comment is talking about something slightly different.  If (for example), the token is minted, and then say 5 tokens are airdropped, \"Remotely destruct\" should be active.  But if all 5 of these tokens are then remotely destructed, then the \"Remotely destruct\" button should become inactive again because there are no instances of this token in existence that can be remotely destructed.\r\n\r\nSo I think this button being active should be tied to \"are there instances of this token in existence that can be remotely destructed?\", not has the token minting been completed or not.\r\n\r\nOf course the \"Airdrop\" button should always be active as long as:\r\nA) the 'minting' (contract deployment) of the token is complete\r\n\r\nAND\r\n\r\nB) there are tokens available to airdrop (e.g. this button should become inactive again if the token has a finite supply, and 100% of that finite supply has already been airdropped, so there are no tokens remaining to airdrop).\r\n\r\nSo the logic that determines if the \"Airdrop\" button is active/inactive and if the \"Remotely destruct\" button is active/inactive should be different.",
